            <li><WikiLink slug="pages/Starbursts" text="Starburst Galaxies" /> - Galaxies with enhanced star formation rates</li>
            <li><WikiLink slug="pages/Star_Formation_UV" text="Ultraviolet Observations of Star Formation" /> - UV as a star formation tracer</li>
            <li><WikiLink slug="pages/Hickson_Compact_Groups" text="Hickson Compact Groups" /> - Dense groups of galaxies</li>
            <li><WikiLink slug="pages/Spectral_Energy_Distribution" text="Spectral Energy Distribution Modeling" /> - SED fitting techniques</li>
            <li><WikiLink slug="pages/AstroSat_Mission" text="AstroSat and UVIT" /> - Space-based UV observations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="section-5">Open Questions</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Is the candidate tidal dwarf truly bound, or will it disperse in the future?</li>
            <li>What is the detailed star formation history of the tidal dwarf relative to its parent galaxies?</li>
            <li>How do metallicities in tidal dwarfs compare to the primary galaxies?</li>
            <li>What is the timescale for the interaction, and how many orbital encounters have occurred?</li>
            <li>Will PGC 56121 and PGC 56125 undergo a major merger, or do they have marginally bound orbits?</li>
        </ul>

